Dear Snow, Please Stick :D

Take the test!

145

Take the test!

OH GOD TORCHWOOD.

I AM SO EXCITED FOR YOU.

COME TO MUMMY.

I CAN'T WAIT UNTIL THURSDAY.

NO SLEEP. NO SLEEP. NO SLEEP. 

NO SLEEP UNTIL I'VE WATCHED THEM ALL AGAIN.

I should be studying or at least writing.

Instead, I have for you yet another soundtrack to 'my life'. It's amusing. So I keep doing it. With select playlists. This one is my 'happy play list'.

Opening Credits – Hell Yeah, Montgomery Gentry
 “He gets trampled on my everyone except when he comes in here”

First Date – Lying is the Most Fun a Girl Can Have […], Panic! At the Disco
 “Is it still me that makes you sweat? Am I who you think about in bed?”

Falling in Love – Shores of California, Dresden Dolls
 “And that is why the girl is called a tease. And that is why the guy is called a sleaze. And that’s why God made escort agencies …Everywhere the girls are crying and the boys are masturbating”

Love Scene – If You’re Going Through Hell, Rodney Atkins
 “If you’re going through hell, keep on going. Don’t slow down. If you’re scared, don’t show it.”

Fight Scene – Dance Dance, Fall Out Boy
 “I’m two quarters and a heart down and I don’t wanna forget how your voice sounds.”

Breaking Up – Necessary Evil, Dresden Dolls
 “I remember golden days when all this was a mystery”

Making Up – The Devil Goes Down to Georgia, Charlie Daniels Band
 “I told you once, you son of a bitch, I’m the best there’s ever been”

Secret Love – Spaceship Superstar, Prism
 “You’re so damn tired and uninspired doing all these one night stands.”

Life's Okay – All These Things That I’ve Done, The Killers
 “I want to mean it from the back of my broken hand. … I’m so much older than I can take. Well, my affection comes and goes I need direction to perfection …”

Mental Breakdown – Miss Independent, Kelly Clarkson
 “What is this feeling taking over? … What happened to Miss Independent?”

Driving – Can’t Fight the Moonlight, Leann Rimes
 “If you think that you won’t fall, well just wait until the sun goes down.”

Learning a Lesson – Sea of No Cares, Great Big Sea
 “Let yourself go with the tide. There’s an angel by your side tonight.”

Deep Thought – Drinkin’ Thinkin’, George Canyon
 “That’s just drinkin’ thinkin’, liquor logic in a can. Your brain cells harden and your body believes you’re super man. That’s just drinkin’ thinkin’ and here’s where the trouble starts. The more you think the better you drink you are.”

Flashback – Ding Dong Song (Tra la la), Gunther
 “Oh, you touch my tra la la. Mm my ding ding dong. Me, being denied. I’m looking for some love. … You tease me, oh please me. I want you to be my love toy. Come near me, don’t fear me. I just can’t get enough of you boy.”

Happy Dance – How Could I Forget, The Faint
 “Introverted boy you are an interesting boy, think you’re intellectual but no one’s talking to you now. I might be an introvert to you a shallow fashionestra. Deep as any paper plate, dressed just like the girl beside you.”

Regretting – Here Comes My Baby, Great Big Sea
 “In the midnight moonlight hour, I keep walking along that lonely mile. And every time I do I keep seeing this picture of you ... Here comes my baby, here she comes now. And it comes to no surprise to me, with another guy.”

Long Night Alone – Somebody Told Me, The Killers
 “Somebody told me that you had a boyfriend that looked like a girlfriend that I had in February of last year. It’s not confidential that I’ve got potentional … Ready, let’s roll onto something new. Taking it’s toll and I’m leaving without you.”

Final Battle – Soccer Practice, Gay Pimp
 “Hey dude, I was thinking we could go do something dirty. He dude, I was thinking we could go do something dirty … I like to do manly things but I like baby to do them with you. I was thinking we could go do something dirty.”
 
Death Scene – My Give A Damn’s Busted, Jo Dee Messina
 “I really wanna care. I wanna feel something. Let me dig a little deeper. Nah, sorry. Nothing.”

Closing Credits – I’m a Bitch, Meredith Brooks
 “I hate the world today. You’re so good to me, I know but I can’t change. Tried to tell you but you look at me like maybe I’m an angel underneath – innocent and sweet. Yesterday I cried. You must have been relieved to see the softer side. I can understand how you’d be so confused. I don’t envy you. I’m a little bit of everything all rolled into one.”

Another new illness to watch out for! 
? 

A woman calls her boss one morning and tells him that she is staying home
because she is not feeling well. 

"What's the matter?" he asks. 

"I have a case of anal glaucoma," she says in a weak voice. 

"What the hell is anal glaucoma?" 


"I can't see my ass coming into work today." 


 .... oh my mother. Sending Jo mixed signals
